[{"id":"FT536854","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"The shaded areas on the map most likely indicate regions that are affected or threatened by which of the following?","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<img alt=\"The figure shows a map of North America. There are shaded areas on the map. A key titled Areas at Risk indicates that areas with the darkest shading are at Very High Risk areas with medium shading are at High Risk and areas with light shading are at Moderate Risk. The very high risk areas include: the Central Valley of California, Southern California, and the Mexican states of Baja California, Guanajuato, Queretaro, and Hidalgo. The high risk areas include Utah, Arizona, southern New Mexico, West Texas, the mouth of the Rio Grande, and in Mexico the states of Baja California Sur, Sonora, Sinaloa, Coahuila, Zacatecas, YucatÃ¡n, and the southern half of Veracruz state. The moderate risk areas include south central British Columbia and the prairie regions of Alberta and Saskatchewan in Canada, eastern Washington, eastern Oregon and Idaho, the Great Plains of the United States, and Nuevo Leon in Mexico.\" height=\"272\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/8568d18f800728a3babbba72cb7ca12a/original.png\" width=\"450\">"}],"choicesHtml":["<p>Depopulation</p>","<p>Deforestation</p>","<p>Desertification</p>","<p>Deindustrialization</p>","<p>Devolution</p>"],"answer":1}]